public class SLDProtocolHandler1_0_0
extends SLDProtocolHandler

Implements the main class for the SLD implementation specification (version 1.0.0) which starts the parsing of the styled layer descriptor document in order to store all the information that it has inside and transform it into objects.

An SLD document is defined as a sequence of styled layers.

The version attribute gives the SLD version an SLD document, to facilitate backward compatibility with static documents stored in various different versions of an SLD spec.

The Styled layers can correspond to either named layers or user-defined layers, which are described in subsequent sections. There may be any number of either type of styled layer, including zero, mixed in any order.
